# Commit Message Guidelines

## Language

Always write commit messages in English.

## Format

<prefix> <type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>

### Prefix

Must include [be] to indicate that this commit belongs to the backend project.

### Types
- feat: add new feature
- fix: fix bug
- docs: update documentation
- style: code formatting, missing semicolons, etc. (no code changes)
- refactor: refactor code
- test: add/update test code
- chore: update build process, package manager configuration, etc.

### Scope

Optionally specify which part was changed.
For example: (api), (core), (ui), (db)

### Subject
- Keep it within 50 characters.
- Use present tense (e.g., “change” instead of “changed”).
- Start with a lowercase letter.
- Do not end with a period.

### Body (optional)
- Keep each line within 72 characters.
- Explain the reason for the change and how it differs from previous behavior.

### Footer (optional)
- Specify any breaking changes.
- Reference closed issues.

### Example

[be] feat(auth): add social login feature

Implement Google and Facebook login using OAuth2.
Add automatic synchronization of user profile information.

Closes #123